	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aye, getting my faction up with King Tormax took a grand total of 3 days (would be less if'n I was higher level).&nbsp;&nbsp;First I hunted the low end dorfs in East Wastes and Great Divide and brought their heads back to the Recruiter.  After a day of that I was warmly with the frost giants and indifferent to the storm giants.  I then hunted in Skyshrine and after just 2 hours I was warmly to the storm giants.  <br><br>The rest of the 2nd day and all of the 3rd (a "day" being my 6 - 8 hours of playing that I can manage if I put my mind to it) was just me delivering supplies to Great Divide.  The trade run for Great Divide has 2 parts that raise your faction with King Tormax, and since GD is so close to Kael Drakkal, it was just pay 500gp, run to GD, gate to Kael Drakkal, run back to GD to complete the last leg of the quest, and gate back to start all over again.  Lather, rinse, repeat.  As long as you have enough cash, you can essentially buy your faction with these quests.  <br><br>Once you're indifferent to the King faction, all of the fun (and huge faction) quests become available.  You'll be doing the quests anyway at this point, so the faction is just a nice bonus.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
